{
  "stem": "20083.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And both of them were dear people-- I have to be absolutely honest about it-- even my stepmother, even though I never referred to her as Stepmother or Stiefmutter, but as Tante, as Aunt, Tante Ida.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But since she was a, a really decent woman, I had harbored no ill feelings toward her.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was very, very sad to leave both of them, too, especially my father, since he had that stroke and was completely lame on one side.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it had to be done.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I remember him standing on the balcony and waving to me as I left.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that balcony still exists.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In fact, I was standing on it about two years ago.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as I said, my sister was 10 years older than I was.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was nothing that could be done, because she was considered an adult, just like my mother.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And even though they put their names down on several lists to emigrate, as I said, to France, Belgium, Holland, England, the United States, the waiting period was a tremendous number of years, as far as the United States was concerned, I think eight years in 1938.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they said, yes, your number will be up in 1946.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's when you will be able to emigrate.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Of course, by that time, my mother had been gassed in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But while you were going away, were you aware of any plans afoot to help your sister to survive or not?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You left just leaving your mother and sister, knowing that they are just going to be--",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, since my-- you, you are absolutely right with that question.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
